      <abstract>
        <label>Abstract</label>
        <p><italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Emesopsis</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">infenestra</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Tatarnic, Wall &amp; Cassis, 2011 (<tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="subordo">Heteroptera</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name>: <tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="familia">Reduviidae</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name>) is reported from New Zealand for the first time, based on a single specimen collected alive in the wild in Auckland in June 2013. The species was previously known only from Australia (Queensland) and the Loyalty Islands (New Caledonia).</p>
