  <body>
    <sec sec-type="Introduction">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <p><italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Emesopsis</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">infenestra</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Tatarnic, Wall &amp; Cassis, 2011 was originally described from Australia (2 specimens, including holotype) and the Loyalty Islands (2 specimens). Nothing else has been published about it. As far as I am aware, it has never before been collected from New Zealand.</p>
    </sec>
